'''Alyson Court''' was born in Toronto, Canada on [[November 9]], [[1973]]. At the age of 11, she voiced the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] character [[Malani]] in the [[1985]] [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] animated television series.

Her best-known appearance was [[Wikipedia:The Big Comfy Couch|''The Big Comfy Couch'']]. She also appeared on such television shows and movies as ''The Care Bears'', ''Madballs'', ''The New Archies'', ''X-Men'', ''Timothy Goes to School'', ''Stranger in My Bed'', ''Beetlejuice'', ''Drop Out Mother'', ''Silver Surfer'' and ''Clifford the Big Red Dog''. She also voiced Mira Clay, Soon, and other characters in ''Bakugan''. Her favorite movie appearance was a live-action video called ''My Pet Monster'' (also an animated TV series) in which she costars with Yannick Bisson, Colin Fox and Sunny Besen Thrasher.

